The paper discusses the use of a synaptic model to improve continual learning in reinforcement learning agents. This topic is closely related to machine learning (cs.LG), neural networks (cs.NE), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of a biological model for synapses also suggests a systems biology (cs.SY) or computational neuroscience (cs.CV) perspective.
